###- QUICK AND DIRTY: COMPILATION AND INSTALLATION -############################
  You'll need curie-4, including icemake...

    $ icemake -dif /usr


################################################################################


NOTE:
  This is an early version of this library; It has not been tested properly, and
  is rather intended as an API snapshot.

NOTE.2:
  Please take note of the library licence (the COPYING file), as well as the
  credits (the CREDITS file).


###- DETAILS -##################################################################

Compilation:
  Make sure you have libcurie-4 or higher installed, then:

    $ icemake

  A number of compilation options are available if you run into issues. To see
  them, use:

    $ icemake --help

Installation:
  use this command to install regularly (for example into /usr, in the example):

    $ icemake -dif /some/prefix

Linking against libduat without using icemake:
  Use pkg-config to retrieve the flags needed to link with libduat:

    $ pkg-config --cflags --libs libduat

  For the hosted variant of libcurie, use:

    $ pkg-config --cflags --libs libduat-hosted

  Check pkg-config's documentation for more details.

CONTACT:
  Best bet is IRC: freenode #kyuba
